{
  "texts": [
    "The study was conducted in two phases.",
    "First, PSTs were asked to solve the mathematical word problem individually using various strategies such as visualization, table, and guess, check, and refine techniques suitable for primary school children aged between five and 11.",
    "In the second phase, the same mathematical problem was presented to ChatGPT, with prompts specifically tailored to reflect the context of primary school children.",
    "This study was conducted within the school of education at an Australian regional university that prepares early childhood, primary, and secondary school teachers.",
    "The study focused on PSTs who were in the final year of their degree program and were being prepared to teach children from foundation (with an average age of five years) to year 6 (with an average age of 11 years)."
  ]
}